subject: RE: [junit] New poll for junit
msgSnippet: That was fun.  I voted against it.  Let us know the results, will you? I imagine most people will if they re like me -- I keep tabs on a number of news sites
messageBody:
That was fun. I voted against it. Let us know the results, will you?

I imagine most people will if they're like me -- I keep tabs on a number
of news sites and news/email groups. So stuff like the message below is
something I would probably see on theserverside.com or java.sun.com or
maybe IBM's DeveloperWorks for Java.

Keep this list for JUnit (of course, I'm all for pretty much any
JUnit-related announcements).

Scott Stirling
Framingham, MA

> From: junit@yahoogroups.com [mailto:junit@yahoogroups.com]
